      <item>
        <title>Tragedies of Life</title>
        <description>&lt;h1 id=&quot;unfortunate-tragedies-of-life&quot;&gt;Unfortunate Tragedies of Life&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;You will be most recognized and most appreciated after you die&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;People close to you will frequently lie to you (as they logically should), yet strangers will always tell you the truth as they have no incentive to lie&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;If you are attracted to someone, openly showing your attraction to them will destroy your chances of being with them&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Most skills required to have a job cannot be learned in school, yet school is so expensive that it requires a job to pay for it&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;While it’s very fulfilling to exercise and work hard to look better, people with naturally high levels of human growth hormone will be muscular without putting in the effort and time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h1 id=&quot;fortunate-blessings-of-life&quot;&gt;Fortunate Blessings of Life&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;It’s virtually impossible to die due to lack of money (at least in Canada), which can give some people a sense of freedom&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Life is long enough to see significant technological advancement in one’s lifetime&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Because of the high connectivity caused by the internet, it’s relatively easy to start a business, market a product, distribute art, write literature, and in general have an impact on the world&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
